<HR size="1" color="#a62a2a">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I've had something similar happen with a character of mine on the Sister's Island. I jumped ship to grab Kiola nuts and then ran back to the ship to catch it before it left. If you're fast, you can do this easily. However, there is a pirate that spawns near the hut where the nuts are sold, and if he's close enough, he may aggro. He's green to my character, but he aggro'd anyway. I ran to the ship figuring he'd lay off once aboard, I never attacked him once, but he followed. So I attacked him so I could kill him before he did any damage to the other passengers. Have you ever tried fighting on the boat? Some of the worst pathing in the game. You can have the guy standing right in front of you and you won't be able to hit him. When he finally got low on hp's, I chased him all over the place, including below decks, all the while getting messages that he's too far away to hit, and I'm right next to him! Then, go cap it off, the boat zones to BB, and the game boots me. Back to Sister's Isle. I didn't know NPC's would follow you onto the ship, or I never would have dragged it there. Hope this helps everyone to avoid similar mistakes.<P>
</FONT>
